Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.08,0:00:06.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Due to Ran's absence, Uncle and\NI wound up eating out for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.88,0:00:11.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After seeing some flyers, we decided to\Nhead to Haido City for some ramen.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.72,0:00:17.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Flaunting a "Good it's To Die For" slogan, will\Nthis shabby-looking shop really be all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.39,0:00:21.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention that Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, a customer who arrived after us...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.77,0:00:25.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was a real estate agent who plotted\Nto land-shark this shopping street.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.45,0:00:31.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alienated by owner Ogura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, assistant Sayo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and\Nthe adjacent barbershop manager Taninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.52,0:00:26.77,Signs,,0,0,0,,Ogura Katsumasa (49)\N"Ramen Ogura" Owner
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.77,0:00:28.36,Signs,,0,0,0,,Oohashi Sayo (28)\NPart-time Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.98,0:00:31.82,Signs,,0,0,0,,Taninaka Atsushi (47)\NBarbershop Owner
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.32,0:00:33.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had soured the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.30,0:00:38.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite its shabby appearance and hostile atmosphere...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.07,0:00:39.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The shop's ramen was one-of-a-kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.62,0:00:43.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The slogan "So Good It's To Die For" was true to its words.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.75,0:00:50.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, after eating some of the ramen,\NSaizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} suddenly let out an anguished cry...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.59,0:00:52.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And actually died.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.63,0:00:56.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cause of death was hydrocyanic poisoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.97,0:00:58.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was this murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.30,0:01:02.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If so, the culprit would have to be someone in this shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.61,0:01:16.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I Love You Miss Mystery - the one now in an endless labyrinth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.20,0:01:22.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's embrace this love and solve puzzle right now
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.20,0:01:26.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If all cases were men...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.83,0:01:28.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose the invisible mysteries would be women.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.79,0:01:30.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspiration hits me when I enter the shop...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.25,0:01:32.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Death Lord ramen shall speak of the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.38,0:01:33.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.88,0:01:35.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.80,0:01:37.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.34,0:03:07.89,Signs,,0,0,0,,(PART TWO)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.34,0:03:07.89,Signs,,0,0,0,,RAMEN SO GOOD IT'S TO DIE FOR
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.14,0:03:12.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.15,0:03:15.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.36,0:03:16.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.82,0:03:21.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No poison was detected inside the ramen in question.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.95,0:03:25.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Neither was any found in the water the victim drank...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.91,0:03:31.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nor on the decorative flowers at the victim's\Nseat, nor the glass they were arranged in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.66,0:03:35.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means Sayo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} and I are cleared from suspicion, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.59,0:03:36.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.05,0:03:40.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the thumb and index finger of the victim's left hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.51,0:03:42.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And on the chopsticks the victim used, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.72,0:03:46.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Atop the table at his seat, toxicity tests came back positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.93,0:03:52.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, the poison detected on the chopsticks\Nand on the table were but a trace amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.48,0:03:53.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.56,0:03:58.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We found the same toxic powder from\Nthe inside pocket of the victim's jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.44,0:03:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you have any clues?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.65,0:04:04.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Such as, if you had seen Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} put his hand in his inside pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.66,0:04:07.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, can't say that I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.83,0:04:12.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if that's the case, wouldn't that man have applied\Nthe poison on his finger himself and licked it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.87,0:04:15.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me, Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.12,0:04:16.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He did say this before he collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.75,0:04:20.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"My company is going down in flames, it makes me feel like dying."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.55,0:04:26.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, that bastard also went on about\Nhow he should poison our ramen and destroy our shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.84,0:04:28.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.64,0:04:32.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bet he was trying to put poison in the ramen\Nbut ended up accidentally ingesting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.85,0:04:37.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems the possibility this was a suicide or an accident still exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.19,0:04:38.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.48,0:04:40.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apologies, but Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.86,0:04:41.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.19,0:04:45.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you come inside and explain everything once again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.11,0:04:47.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.53,0:04:48.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I'll go too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.16,0:04:48.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.37,0:04:51.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kids shouldn't get in the way of adults' work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.41,0:04:52.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.46,0:04:58.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right just let the detectives do their investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.54,0:05:00.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not something for a kid to see!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.92,0:05:04.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, if you all would stand by outside for a few more moments.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.30,0:05:05.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.13,0:05:11.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So there wasn't any poison on Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s other\Nbelongings, besides on his inside jacket pocket?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.22,0:05:12.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.97,0:05:16.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We examined his handkerchief, wallet, cigarettes, and lighter...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.85,0:05:19.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even the glasses that had fallen to the ground, but got nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.02,0:05:25.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, was there anyone among the three who had\Nanything suspicious on them from the body search?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.66,0:05:29.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like a container that could've held the poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.62,0:05:31.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.58,0:05:37.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All Manager Ogura had on him were\Ncigarettes, a lighter, and a portable ashtray.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.79,0:05:42.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The part-timer Oohashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had a cell phone,\Na handkerchief, eye drops, and a purse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.34,0:05:48.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Taninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from the barbershop only had\Nhis wallet, glasses, and the keys to his shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.84,0:05:50.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the contents of the eye drops?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.68,0:05:54.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We did examine that, but they were just ordinary eye drops.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.14,0:06:00.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Incidentally, Manager Ogura's cigarettes were\Njust enough for a quick puff after closing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.27,0:06:04.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Taninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s glasses are apparently\Nreading glasses he seldom wears.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.61,0:06:05.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And by the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.86,0:06:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} collapsed, Manager Ogura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said "Idiot,\Nthink we're gonna fall for that same trick again?" but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.66,0:06:15.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have there been other cases like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.12,0:06:16.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.20,0:06:18.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems it has happened twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.46,0:06:20.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A fuss over food poisoning at this shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.54,0:06:25.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first time, Oohashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} called an\Nambulance and it caused a big commotion...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.88,0:06:28.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was deemed a malingering by the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.59,0:06:35.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The second time, Manager Ogura and Taninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who happened\Nto be there threw a collapsed customer out of the shop...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.60,0:06:38.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that customer picked himself up and cursed them out as he left.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.90,0:06:46.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I was told that those two customers\Nwere both hired by Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to cause trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.74,0:06:50.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll go back inside and continue with the investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.91,0:06:53.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.62,0:06:56.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I still have questions to ask yo—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.96,0:06:59.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, not again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.67,0:07:02.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not all right if you don't wait outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.13,0:07:05.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Boy, you've watched too many mystery dramas!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.96,0:07:09.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Think you're like the young Kobayashi of the Boy Detectives' Club?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.92,0:07:14.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, rather than young Kobayashi...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.10,0:07:16.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel like the one who has seen it all...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.18,0:07:19.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akechi Kogoro, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.19,0:07:24.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to our investigation...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.69,0:07:28.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was no poison inside of the ramen the deceased Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} ate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.40,0:07:33.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Neither did the water nor the glass that was\Nbrought to him before he ordered ramen...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.24,0:07:40.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nor the decorative flowers on the seat where\NSaizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} sat, nor the glass they were arranged in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.66,0:07:48.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where poison was detected, however, was on the\Nleft-handed Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s left thumb and left index finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.09,0:07:53.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although there was also poison detected on the\Nchopsticks he used and on the tabletop where he sat...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.26,0:07:55.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can exclude those due to the minuscule amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.60,0:08:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, out of Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s belongings, no poison was on his\Nhandkerchief, wallet, glasses, cigarettes, or lighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.60,0:08:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we found powdered poison in his inside jacket pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.27,0:08:10.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Further, the fact that before Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.90,0:08:17.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said things like "I feel like dying," and "I'll destroy this shop\Nby poisoning the ramen," if we take those into account...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.95,0:08:22.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would've most likely touched the\Npoison he put in his inside jacket pocket...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.62,0:08:28.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And either committed suicide or was\Nplotting to lace the ramen with poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.50,0:08:31.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thus, this case is not a homicide—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.38,0:08:33.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm, Inspector...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.72,0:08:39.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Other than on Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fingers, wasn't\Nthere poison on the chopsticks and table?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.51,0:08:43.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, wouldn't it be too early to\Ndetermine that it wasn't a homicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.06,0:08:48.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was sitting at the seat of the\Nregular customer who died a short while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.40,0:08:54.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it seems that Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} often purposely\Nsat at that seat as a form of harassment, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.86,0:08:58.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if his seat could've been predicted\Nin advance, the conclusion is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.53,0:09:04.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I already said this, but the amount of poison detected\Non the chopsticks and table was insignificant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.79,0:09:08.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've no choice but to think he touched\Nthose with his poison-laced hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.42,0:09:13.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention, the other chopsticks in the\Nchopstick stand had no poison on them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.13,0:09:17.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would've been impossible to pinpoint a place on\Nthe chopsticks or table for the victim to touch!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.68,0:09:19.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good point...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.27,0:09:25.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ramen, chow mein...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.27,0:09:28.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you'll excuse me, man...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.40,0:09:31.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.57,0:09:34.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's gotten into it his usual trance-like state!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.86,0:09:38.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just me putting him to sleep with my tranquilizer gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.74,0:09:40.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, is he all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.83,0:09:43.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His dizziness looked pretty awful, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.49,0:09:46.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Almost as if he was a puppet who'd had his strings cut...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.33,0:09:50.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, a puppet indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.29,0:09:54.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't mean me, but Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did have someone pulling his strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.05,0:09:59.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the time he entered this shop, it was\Nas if he'd been possessed by a devil...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.68,0:10:03.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To apply poison to his own finger, and then bring it to his mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.18,0:10:07.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as the culprit among us expected!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.44,0:10:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you telling me that one of these\Nthree is a hypnotist or something ofithe sort?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.57,0:10:18.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, to say that he had been possessed\Nby a devil was just a metaphor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.86,0:10:23.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thee truth is, the culprit took advantage of the\Nfact that people under a certain condition...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.66,0:10:26.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would invariably do something specific upon entering a ramen shop!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.66,0:10:31.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Invariably do something specific"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.29,0:10:37.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you mean every customer that enters a\Nramen shop will put their hand into their inside pocket...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.55,0:10:42.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The poison in his inside pocket was a fake planted\Nby the culprit, in order to make it look like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.18,0:10:48.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit probably prepared something very\Nsimilar to one of Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s belongings...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.10,0:10:52.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Applied poison on it, and switched the two\Nduring the confusion after the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.81,0:10:55.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By "switched," you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.44,0:10:56.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.53,0:10:59.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet the culprit still has it on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.03,0:11:02.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s item with the poison on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.91,0:11:07.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll check them again...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.37,0:11:10.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a way to figure it out soon even without doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.50,0:11:16.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just have them use those items the\Nsame way Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did, right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.34,0:11:18.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.76,0:11:25.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If forced to use an item of Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s, which the culprit\Nwasn't used to using, they'd likely give themselves away, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.14,0:11:25.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.97,0:11:28.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall, all three people have something...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.31,0:11:31.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That duplicated what Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.69,0:11:35.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Manager Ogura had cigarettes and a lighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.48,0:11:38.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sayo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had a handkerchief.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.48,0:11:40.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Taninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had a wallet and glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.45,0:11:49.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.95,0:11:53.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's have Manager Ogura light one of his cigarettes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.29,0:11:55.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sayo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} fold her handkerchief...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.54,0:11:59.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Taninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, for the time being, put on his glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.96,0:12:02.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, in the same manner as the left-handed Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.72,0:12:03.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With their left hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.30,0:12:07.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, everyone, if you would please.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.31,0:12:11.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, see here...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.98,0:12:14.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said the culprit would be revealed this away, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.77,0:12:17.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since we're originally right-handed...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.15,0:12:20.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way we could do it well with our left hands...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.40,0:12:22.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah-le-le?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.57,0:12:24.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.11,0:12:26.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your glasses are crooked!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.24,0:12:30.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I said, I can't really put them on correctly with my left hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.04,0:12:35.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because you're not firmly holding the connective\Npoint where the frame and temple meet, like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.50,0:12:39.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So can you try putting them on again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.80,0:12:43.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got no choice...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.68,0:12:46.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There you go again!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.68,0:12:49.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're grabbing onto the end of the temple!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.27,0:12:53.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why aren't you holding over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.35,0:12:55.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.85,0:12:57.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or you just...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.65,0:12:59.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Won't hold it there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.15,0:13:01.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since that's where the poison is?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.49,0:13:07.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, check those glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.91,0:13:09.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.33,0:13:13.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you would please.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.87,0:13:19.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, isn't this strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.67,0:13:25.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since Taninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came into this shop, he\Nnever even came close to that Saizu bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.05,0:13:26.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.68,0:13:31.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In between Taninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and that man was the little boy's group.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.76,0:13:35.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way he could've ever touched, or\Neven come close to that man, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.06,0:13:39.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, how on earth could he have laced poison onto his glasses!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.27,0:13:40.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.40,0:13:43.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,True, it would've been difficult for him to do so here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.36,0:13:48.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if Taninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did it in his\Nbarbershop, it would've been an easy task.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.66,0:13:52.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, he did say this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.79,0:13:59.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had his hair cut at Taninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nbarbershop just before he came here to eat ramen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.25,0:14:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.00,0:14:06.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At a barbershop, it's only natural for the barber to hold\Nonto your glasses and jacket while your hair is being cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.42,0:14:15.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For Taninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, there would've been enough opportunities\Nto poison his glasses and plant poison in his jacket!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.52,0:14:17.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.73,0:14:23.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll concede it to you for argument's sake, but how\Nthe hell was he able to make Saizu touch there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.36,0:14:26.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it wasn't like he was hypnotized or anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.28,0:14:28.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way he'd so conveniently touch it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.57,0:14:29.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He definitely would touch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.35,0:14:34.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.87,0:14:36.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When in the world did you get outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.58,0:14:39.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because when people with glasses...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.50,0:14:44.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Walk into ramen shops or warm places, immediately...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.88,0:14:48.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This will happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.80,0:14:51.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Condensation!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.26,0:14:57.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, if your glasses cloud up...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.23,0:15:01.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Normally you'll do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.15,0:15:02.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.40,0:15:07.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If his glasses clouded up due to condensation, he'd take them\Noff in order to wipe it with a handkerchief or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.24,0:15:10.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when the poison got onto his fingers!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.99,0:15:14.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was left-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.20,0:15:19.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he took his handkerchief and wiped using his left hand,\Npoison should've also gotten onto his handkerchief.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.16,0:15:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was ambidextrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.08,0:15:26.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said that his parents tried to correct his left-handedness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.92,0:15:30.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he used his right hand to\Nwipe the spilled water on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.80,0:15:34.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he wouldn't be comfortable without\Nusing his left hand while eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.43,0:15:38.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In short, when Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} entered this shop...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.14,0:15:40.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He took off his fogged glasses with his left hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.93,0:15:43.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And took out his handkerchief with his right hand and wiped them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.94,0:15:47.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not at all expecting that poison had been applied to his glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.94,0:15:53.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, if he had used his left hand to take out his handkerchief...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.53,0:15:55.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.24,0:15:58.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was ambidextrous, there's an equal\Nchance for him to use either hand to take it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.16,0:16:00.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.37,0:16:04.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The handkerchief was inside his jacket's left chest pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.88,0:16:09.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he's ambidextrous, he'd use his right\Nhand to take it out since it'd be easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.46,0:16:16.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the tabletop having traces of poison, it was because\Nhe touched it with his left hand while seating himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.60,0:16:23.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, as he was ready to eat ramen and took chopsticks from\Nthe chopstick stand, some poison also got onto there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.39,0:16:28.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As he used his mouth to break apart those\Nchopsticks, poison stuck onto his lips and teeth...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.94,0:16:34.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As soon as he slurped up his ramen, the\Npoison entered his system just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.74,0:16:43.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Incidentally, the reason Taninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} passed the chopsticks\Nto us is because he didn't want Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.87,0:16:50.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he had used his poisoned hand to pass the chopsticks\Nto us, we might have also been poisoned to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.17,0:16:55.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're saying that he came to the shop to make sure\Nno innocent customers would get dragged into it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.88,0:16:57.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.97,0:17:01.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just when could Taninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} have switched the glasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.22,0:17:04.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he hadn't switched them, the trick\Nwould've been found out in no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.89,0:17:06.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Switching the glasses was done...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.85,0:17:12.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Manager Ogura and Taninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were about\Nto throw the collapsed Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} out of the shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.24,0:17:18.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, upon Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s collapse, the\Nglasses flew to the ground near his legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.37,0:17:24.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,ForTaninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who had squatted near Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nlegs in order to lift the lower part of his body...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.62,0:17:28.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had the opportunity to switch the\Nglasses and block our view with his body.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.75,0:17:31.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.34,0:17:34.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't it only by chance that his glasses flew off?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.34,0:17:38.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If his glasses had remained firmly on his face,\Nwouldn't it have been difficult to switch them?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.43,0:17:43.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of the two incidents of food poisoning\Nthat had occurred in this shop...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.85,0:17:51.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The second time, Manager Ogura and Taninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} threw the\Ncustomer who had pretended to have\Nfood poisoning out of the shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.65,0:17:57.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this time, he could predict that Manager Ogura\Nwould do the same thing when Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.82,0:18:01.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That the manager would ask him to\Nhelp throw Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} out into the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.03,0:18:08.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This time, it was by luck that a detective drama obsessed\Nbrat with glasses blurted out, "Don't touch the body!"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.37,0:18:11.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But had it not been for that, he would\Nhave plenty of chance to switch them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.67,0:18:16.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After they cast him out the shop, he could fetch\Nthe glasses that had fallen to the ground...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.47,0:18:19.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or he could rush to the unresponsive Saizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.22,0:18:23.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.76,0:18:28.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The glasses Taninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had on him tested positive for poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.14,0:18:34.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It appears that we've obtained conclusive\Nevidence against you, Taninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.90,0:18:37.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.61,0:18:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's some kind of mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.03,0:18:41.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.66,0:18:43.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Taninaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wouldn't kill anyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.58,0:18:45.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's enough, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.04,0:18:50.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't deserve the privilege of your defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.13,0:18:55.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To kill Saizu in this shop...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.80,0:18:59.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And hopefully thereby ruin this shop was my plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.14,0:19:05.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought that no one would come to a ramen shop\Nwhere someone had been poisoned to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.81,0:19:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why'd you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.93,0:19:12.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haven't we gotten by pretty well these twenty years as neighbors?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.57,0:19:16.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Gotten by pretty well"...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.03,0:19:21.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In these past 20 years, just what have you achieved?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.53,0:19:31.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We worked our rears and souls off in order to raise money, all for\Nthe sake of making this Haido Shopping Street a stylish place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.00,0:19:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you haven't remodeled your shop even once!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.42,0:19:38.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you, I don't have the money...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.30,0:19:42.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Horse-racing, boat-races, road races...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.59,0:19:46.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you had only let up on those a little,\Nyou could've saved up some, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.22,0:19:48.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.64,0:19:54.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you ask my opinion, your profit margin\Non the ramen was way too low!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.15,0:19:58.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without raising the price, you even hired a part-time worker!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.90,0:20:02.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just don't have any business sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.32,0:20:05.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saizu said it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.20,0:20:08.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That the people of the shopping street\Nwere calling this shop the black sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.00,0:20:12.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was actually true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.37,0:20:15.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They asked me many times...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.71,0:20:18.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I could be the one to tell you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.21,0:20:23.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Please either remodel the shop or leave!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.51,0:20:29.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, why didn't you tell us that outright?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.39,0:20:32.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you had, our owner could have...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.23,0:20:33.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't tell you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.27,0:20:38.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I loved the ramen here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.73,0:20:42.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without regard to profit, you steadfastly\Nkept the same taste and price.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.90,0:20:45.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your spirit as an owner radiated.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.75,0:20:56.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, we'll get the rest at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.59,0:21:08.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is my heart talking now, but I believed m you guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.81,0:21:14.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With your ramen, even if you moved elsewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.69,0:21:21.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd definitely keep on prospering...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.37,0:22:58.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One month later...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.16,0:23:02.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Barbershop Taninaka and Ramen Ogura were both demolished.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.67,0:23:06.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the ramen that was so good it was\Nto die for vanished from Haido City.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.84,0:23:07.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.39,0:23:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Ello!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.52,0:23:18.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.98,0:23:20.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.02,0:23:22.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.15,0:23:25.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hear you're a well-known detective here in Beika City!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.98,0:23:28.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, sort of...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.61,0:23:30.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't I be well-known throughout the nation?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.82,0:23:35.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your shop is new, but things look\Nexactly the same as they were before!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.04,0:23:38.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something did change.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.41,0:23:40.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The signboard in front!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.16,0:23:42.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The owner arranged it to suit the latest trend!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.83,0:23:45.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The signboard?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.26,0:23:55.10,Signs,,0,0,0,,So WICKED It's To Die For —\hRamen Ogura
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.26,0:23:55.10,Signs,,0,0,0,,Fo' Sho'
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.10,0:23:58.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"So wicked it's to die for"...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.31,0:24:02.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A fatal fall incident at the haunted hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.02,0:24:03.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this a suicide or a homicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.69,0:24:05.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That intriguing someone finally takes the stage!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.03,0:24:09.90,Signs,,0,0,0,,DEDUCTION SHOWDOWN AT THE HAUNTED HOTEL
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.03,0:24:09.90,Signs,,0,0,0,,(PART ONE)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.42,0:24:27.75,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.42,0:24:29.80,Signs,,0,0,0,,Elevator
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.80,0:24:33.71,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look Forward to the Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.05,0:24:32.18,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next time we have a\Nnew detective-like\Ncharacter!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.18,0:24:33.34,Signs,,0,0,0,,But aren't I more\Nthan enough!?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.34,0:24:37.71,Signs,,0,0,0,,No, not at all...
